Monday Bar Newsletter week 40 In this newsletter: MONDAY BAR CRUISE No 60 JUBILEE, OCTOBER 6-8, 2023 • The cruise is fully booked! • All floors and set times presented. • Theme: Colour Explosion - dress to impress! • Book your dinner, breakfast, brunch now and avoid waiting list • Board the ship from 16.00 (Swedish time). Pre-party on deck 10 • Bring your music box.. but not too big. Nothing that needs wheels… • Don’t forget to bring a valid Passport or National ID • "No 60" Cruise t-shirts and lanyards at C.U.M. Clubwear shop. Bring cash! MONDAY BAR: SISTA NATTEN MED GÄNGET, LÖRDAG 18 NOVEMBER • Last Monday Bar part @ Slakthuset w/ combo trance, hardstyle, psy och techno • Tickets at C.U.M. Clubwear on the cruise: SEK 200 (cash only) Dear Monday Bar family, The cruise is now completely sold out. But there is still a possibility that those of you who have booked a A, B or E cabin for only 2 people could upgrade to 3- or 4. Please call the booking office and find out if this is possible. Call 08-666 33 33 and have your booking reference ready. Here’s info how to get to the ferry terminal (Tallink-Silja website). In Swedish: https://se.tallink.com/vartahamnen <https://se.tallink.com/vartahamnen> In English: https://en.tallink.com/stockholm-vartahamnen <https://en.tallink.com/stockholm-vartahamnen> Reminder about passport and National ID!! We’d like to remind you to bring either a valid Passport or a National ID Card to the cruise to prove your identity and what country you are from. Regular ID or Drivers License are NOT valid identification. And please check the expiration date. Dress theme: COLOUR EXPLOSION People have asked if we will have a dress theme at The Last Cruise in October. The previous theme was Black & White, so now we're doing the opposite, COLOUR EXPLOSION!! Our decor will of course be adapted accordingly. And Dominika at C.U.M. is of course willing to help those of you who want some inspiration. BRING CASH - to buy this at C.U.M. CLUBWEAR shop on the cruise: - ”No 60” CRUISE T-SHIRT (300 SEK or 30€). Sizes: S, M, L, XL, 2XL, 3XL, 5XL - TICKETS (200 SEK) for our "Sista Natten med Gänget" party at Slakthuset Saturday November 18. See images below. See you on the cruise! Monday Bar Crew 🥰 Who would have guessed over 20 years ago that we would sail together for the 60th time on the Baltic sea! We’ll, here we are, and it’s time again to board the best party ship of the Tallink-Silja fleet, M/S Baltic Queen. The cruise is in the beginning of October, but thanks to an outside sun deck partly covered with a roof and wind shield we should be able to enjoy a daytime party on deck while in port in Tallinn on Saturday. YOU NEED A VALID NATIONAL ID CARD or PASSPORT TO BOARD THE SHIP (Driver licence or regular ID card is not allowed) The get onboard, you need to prove your age and identity, but you also need to show what country you are from. It’s probably not possible order new ID/passport at this late stage, so if you don’t have this you can transfer the booking to someone else before the cruise. Call the booking office and have the booking reference available: +46 8 666 33 33 Valid identification are: - Passport - National ID card Not valid: - Regular ID card - Driver license BOOK YOU DINNER NOW TO AVOID WAITING LIST (cheaper) Tallink-Silja has asked us to remind all to pre-book your meals (dinner, breakfast, brunch). That way you will be assured that you can have dinner at the best time for you. With this many people on board the restaurants will fill up quickly and there will be a waiting list if you haven't pre-booked. Please call the booking department with your booking reference handy. Tallink Silja booking office: +46 (0)8-666 33 33 You can also reserve tables online. Have your booking reference ready: In Swedish: https://se.tallink.com/hitta-resa <https://se.tallink.com/hitta-resa> In English: https://en.tallink.com/en/book-a-cruise <https://en.tallink.com/en/book-a-cruise> Restaurants onboard: Swedish: https://se.tallink.com/baltic-queen#tabs-content-3 <https://se.tallink.com/baltic-queen#tabs-content-3> English: https://en.tallink.com/en/baltic-queen-tallink-cruise-ship-stockholm-tallinn#tabs-content-2 <https://en.tallink.com/en/baltic-queen-tallink-cruise-ship-stockholm-tallinn#tabs-content-2> BOARD THE SHIP FROM 16.00 Boarding starts from 16.00. Last time to board is 17.10 and cruise then leaves at 17.30 sharp. But the party already starts at 16.00 at Disco Ibiza, deck 10. The sundeck next to the dance floor is also open with extra sound. PARKING CLOSE TO THE FERRY TERMINAL There’s a car park next to the ferry terminal. But make sure you are in good time since the traffic in Stockholm can be congested Friday afternoon. Especially if there’s a strike (see info above). BRING YOUR OWN MUSIC MACHINE - BUT NOT TOO BIG It’s allowed to play music in the cabins, but not too loud so that it disturbs you, neighbours. No music is allowed between 06-10 in the morning. You can bring a music player, but not too big. Computer speakers, ”boom boxes” are ok, but anything that requires wheels to carry onboard will be confiscated when boarding. If it feels too big, it probably is.. CRUISE T-SHIRTS + MONDAY BAR LANYARDS + PARTY TICKETS FOR NOVEMBER 18 - CASH ONLY There will be a limited number of t-shirts with the cruise logo to buy on board, in C.U.M's shop which is open from 10-01 both evenings. There will be men’s sizes from S-5XL and they cost SEK 300/EUR30. Black t-shirt with round neck. There are also Monday Bar Lanyards in different colours on sale for SEK50/EUR5. C.U.M. will also sell 200 SEK cash tickets for our upcoming party ”Sista Natten med Gänget” Saturday November 18 at Slakthuset. Cash only! - See images below. BRING CASH - YOU CAN FIND AN ATM MACHINE AT THE FERRY TERMINAL The merch is sold cash only, so don't forget to bring cash, preferably as even as possible. There is an ATM machine in the terminal, but not on the ship. LINEUP & SET TIMES Here’s the complete lineup and set times - with music styles and set times in minutes. A good idea is to save this image on your phone! All times on the cruise are Estonian +1 hour, so forward your watch/phone 1 hour when boarding the ship, and keep it that way for the duration of the cruise. A good advice is to set the time setting on manual so the time doesn’t change when entering a different time zone. ONLINE BOOKING https://www.tallinksilja.se/monday-bar <https://www.tallinksilja.se/monday-bar> BOOKING BY PHONE Tallink-Silja booking office: +46 (0)8-666 33 33 (Open: Mon-Fri 08.00-20.00, Sat-Sun 08.00-16.00) Booking reference: MBAR MONDAY BAR CRUISE No 60 JUBILEE Friday-Sunday October 6-8, 2023 (2 nights - 41h) M/S Baltic Queen Stockholm-Tallinn-Stockholm Cruise times Departure, Stockholm Tallink-Silja ferry terminal, Värtahamnen Friday, October 6, 17:30 (5:30 PM), local Swedish time Arrival, Tallinn Tallink D-terminal Saturday October 7, 10:45 (10:45 AM), local Estonian time (+1 hour) Departure, Tallinn Tallink D-terminal Saturday October 7, 18:00 (6 PM), local Estonian time (+1 hour) Arrival, Stockholm Tallink-Silja ferry terminal, Värtahamnen Sunday October 8, 10:30 (10:30 AM), local Swedish time Age limit: 18 years when boarding. Cabin prices starting at SEK 1420 per person  <https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCBTe8_DMsFC3HYqEg4suMxg>  <http://facebook.com/mondaybar>  <http://instagram.com/mondaybar>  <http://twitter.com/mondaybar> © Monday Bar, 1992-2023 Box 2254, SE-10316 Stockholm, Sweden Unsubscribe  <https://campaign-preferences.com/unsubscribe/_Ds7OA8sQKIpuyqlOf_C6j91UUuQr9RhaUUVSi-wqYhn_znHCcTE_ximE8FGdug1NgSfO0chp0JvTBhgYaIc8PmMTFSHsmqYV_aJ9blN9J3Gb_0i1A9g3RI0YN6oXSOH-s47NHpNh0cUlAb3qvQTR-IXJOXwacnVj78XhmVLeEqWK0e7Svf8EbGeN7bT1_DXUNV3wWJ3k4QqM_AwncsWAJT9IAajyN7hCH8dZxwD73HS4xk7wzU0j6-M9npB30mwcbVqntZquHJ8eDmqO6oF1Tu_xDIX9QvzZLNr9z5Jy1VTcdl58Wu1j3dAjnO8FkjMUV_oRbbXDDpvJBnDAb0ouEZEwPZoYCuScXphTvKl70DU67lJrC2hYSg=>